IPO Preview: Ferrari N.V. - Ferrari N.V. (NYSE:RACE) | Seeking AlphaSign in / Join NowGO»IPO Preview: Ferrari N.V.Oct.21.15 | About: Ferrari N.V. (RACE) IPOdesktop Value, IPOs, long onlyIPOpremiumSummaryFerrari N.V. is among the leading luxury brands focused on the design, engineering, production and sale of the world's most recognizable luxury performance sports cars.A P/E of 33.5 is high for a car company, but this is a high-end iconic brand. Production has gone up from 7,000 cars in 2013 to 9,000 in 2019.It is selling only 9% on the IPO. No proceeds will go to the company.Introducing the brand to a multitude of consumer items.Based in Maranello (NYSE:MO) Italy, Ferrari N.V. (NYSE:RACE) scheduled an $859 million IPO on the NYSE, with a market capitalization of $9.4 billion, at a price range midpoint of $50, for Wednesday, October 21, 2015. The issue is priced at $52, range top.
The full IPO calendar is available at IPOpremium.
SEC Documents
Manager, Joint-managers: UBS Investment Bank, BofA Merrill Lynch, Allen & Company, Banco Santander, BNP Paribas, J.P. Morgan, MediobancaCo-managers: None
End of lockup (180 days): Monday, April 18, 2016End of 10-day quiet period: Saturday, October 31, 2015
SummaryFerrari is among the leading luxury brands focused on the design, engineering, production and sale of the world's most recognizable luxury performance sports cars.
The brand symbolizes luxury, exclusivity, innovation, state-of-the-art sporting performance and Italian design and engineering heritage
