Ferrari stock price target raised to $100 from $72 at Morgan Stanley
Ferrari stock price target raised to $100 from $72 at Morgan Stanley

May. 8, 2017 at 9:04 a.m. ET
by Tomi Kilgore









Ferrari profit jumps on higher sales volumes
Ferrari NV reported a 60% jump in first quarter profit as the Italian sports car maker continued with plans to slowly increase volume over the coming years. Net income in the three months to the end of March rose to 124 million euros ($135 million) from EUR78 million in the same period last year. Revenue increased 22% to EUR821 million on the increased volume and higher sales of motors to Maserati, the luxury car maker owned by Fiat Chrysler Automobiles NV.

